<comment datatype='string'>Transcription from the &lt;i&gt;ssrS&lt;/i&gt;p1 and &lt;i&gt;ssrS&lt;/i&gt;p2 promoters is regulated in a growth-phase-dependent manner [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23864284&quot;&gt;Lee13a&lt;/a&gt;]. In addition, transcription of &lt;i&gt;ssrS&lt;/i&gt;p1 and &lt;i&gt;ssrS&lt;/i&gt;p2 is feedback activated and feedback inhibited, respectively, and this feedback regulation is Fis dependent [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23864284&quot;&gt;Lee13a&lt;/a&gt;]. The differential feedback regulation could serve to integrate sigma factors, as well as providing a means for maintaining appropriate cellular concentrations of 6S RNA in response to environmental changes [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23864284&quot;&gt;Lee13a&lt;/a&gt;].</comment>
